                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13509282" author="jcoveney" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 22:46:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a fix for it... I&apos;m open to other opinions on how to fix this. I used a ThreadLocal because the JobConf is stored in a ThreadLocal, so I wanted to mirror that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528798" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 08:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jonathan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How about simply removing that warning message?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;jobConf not available. Not tracking UDF timing regardless of user preference.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to the comment for &lt;tt&gt;UdfContext.getJobConf()&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;jobConf&lt;/tt&gt; will be null only if it&apos;s called on the front-end. In that case, I don&apos;t think that this warning message is particularly helpful after all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;     * Get the JobConf.  This should only be called on
     * the backend.  It will &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; on the frontend.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please let me know what you think.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529162" author="jcoveney" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 17:51:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13560973" author="alangates" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 19:16:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Canceling patch since it seems the feedback was to take a different direction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561149" author="jcoveney" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 22:10:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok enough laziness. Here is a patch which removes it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561181" author="daijy" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 22:39:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
